  <article id="budget"><br> <br>
  <h2>Do You Budget?</h2>
  <p>Budgeting is the best thing you can do for your wallet. Oh forgot to mention for yourself as well. It is a wonderful way to be disciplined with your money by pretty much disciplining your moey. It helps you figure out how much money you are expecting to come in an match that money with expenses (or how you plan to spend it.)</p>
  
  <p>Many people find that when they budget they are less likely to over-spend. This is because budgeting is like making a contract with yourself about how to spend our money. This means you get to check up on yourself and keep yourself honest, as it were.</p> 
  
  <p>Budgeting also frees you up to do great and amazing things. I know it may sound coutner-intuitive, but it is true. If you have a goal to go on vacation and you want to save up for it, budgeting is a great way to accomplish this. You can budget to save a certain amount every month or week until you reach your goal, which is way better than scrammbling to get money together at the last minute. One more plus while you are on the vacation you can plan to spend your money well enough that you do not run out or go over.</p>
  <p>So, do you budget?</p>
